WEBVTT

1
00:00:22.170 --> 00:00:25.610
(Transcribed by TurboScribe.ai. Go Unlimited to remove this message.) ACT II.

2
00:00:26.330 --> 00:00:27.070
SCENE I.

3
00:00:27.790 --> 00:00:30.430
Summer pavilion in the palace of the

4
00:00:30.430 --> 00:00:31.770
Marquise de Rotondo.

5
00:00:32.610 --> 00:00:34.950
Dancing going on in different parts of the

6
00:00:34.950 --> 00:00:35.430
stage.

7
00:00:36.370 --> 00:00:39.130
Baritana seated and a group of cavaliers are

8
00:00:39.130 --> 00:00:40.110
standing round her.

9
00:00:41.030 --> 00:00:43.830
Don José standing opposite to her with his

10
00:00:43.830 --> 00:00:45.790
eyes fixed on her, left.

11
00:00:46.630 --> 00:00:49.270
The Marquise and Marchioness paying

12
00:00:49.270 --> 00:00:51.090
attention to their various guests.

13
00:00:51.970 --> 00:00:53.530
Lords and ladies promenading.

14
00:00:54.490 --> 00:00:56.950
Music which dies away as they dance up.

15
00:00:57.710 --> 00:00:59.690
First cavalier to Marquise.

16
00:01:00.090 --> 00:01:03.650
Upon my honour, Marquise, I never saw the

17
00:01:03.650 --> 00:01:05.630
Marchioness looking so well.

18
00:01:05.830 --> 00:01:06.950
And so youthful.

19
00:01:07.390 --> 00:01:09.930
Really, gentlemen, your compliments

20
00:01:09.930 --> 00:01:11.630
overpower me.

21
00:01:12.910 --> 00:01:14.270
Marquise aside.

22
00:01:14.890 --> 00:01:17.050
How you dervish they all are.

23
00:01:17.290 --> 00:01:17.890
Aloud.

24
00:01:19.030 --> 00:01:21.450
You must really come and dine with me

25
00:01:21.450 --> 00:01:21.910
to-morrow.

26
00:01:22.530 --> 00:01:24.510
I want your opinion of some wine of

27
00:01:24.510 --> 00:01:25.450
a rare quality.

28
00:01:25.450 --> 00:01:28.090
And you show so much taste in other

29
00:01:28.090 --> 00:01:30.470
matters that I should value your opinion

30
00:01:30.470 --> 00:01:31.570
very much.

31
00:01:32.370 --> 00:01:33.770
Women and wine, you know.

32
00:01:34.330 --> 00:01:36.670
A judge of the one is generally a

33
00:01:36.670 --> 00:01:37.730
judge of the other.

34
00:01:38.190 --> 00:01:41.210
Don José still gazing on Maritana.

35
00:01:41.630 --> 00:01:43.230
Thoughtful and musing.

36
00:01:43.590 --> 00:01:45.230
Ah, that's well.

37
00:01:45.550 --> 00:01:47.050
Marquise going up to him.

38
00:01:47.570 --> 00:01:50.270
Well, my lord, do admire the fate.

39
00:01:50.990 --> 00:01:52.770
The women are lovely, are they not?

40
00:01:53.450 --> 00:01:57.450
By the by, speaking of lovely women, have

41
00:01:57.450 --> 00:01:58.870
you seen my Marchioness?

42
00:01:59.850 --> 00:02:04.410
Your lordship's eyes seem fixed on my niece.

43
00:02:04.830 --> 00:02:08.169
Yes, how well she sustains her new dignity.

44
00:02:08.889 --> 00:02:11.210
I really think that you and I have

45
00:02:11.210 --> 00:02:14.910
only rectified a little error of destiny in

46
00:02:14.910 --> 00:02:17.430
placing her in the position which is

47
00:02:17.430 --> 00:02:20.950
evidently the one for which nature intended

48
00:02:20.950 --> 00:02:21.330
her.

49
00:02:21.990 --> 00:02:23.410
What is your opinion?

50
00:02:24.130 --> 00:02:26.990
My opinion is that your lordship's opinion

51
00:02:26.990 --> 00:02:29.690
is my opinion, and that you are perfectly

52
00:02:29.690 --> 00:02:30.470
right.

53
00:02:30.770 --> 00:02:33.990
Ah, Marquis, you are quite a courtier.

54
00:02:34.330 --> 00:02:36.510
Your tact is unrivalled.

55
00:02:37.310 --> 00:02:40.050
How go on His Majesty's birds, of which

56
00:02:40.050 --> 00:02:40.910
you are the governor?

57
00:02:41.610 --> 00:02:44.010
I am proud to say that since I

58
00:02:44.010 --> 00:02:45.770
have been at the head of the establishment,

59
00:02:46.430 --> 00:02:48.030
the royal birds have reached an

60
00:02:48.030 --> 00:02:49.810
unprecedented plumpness.

61
00:02:49.810 --> 00:02:54.110
By the by, Don Carlo is seriously ill,

62
00:02:54.290 --> 00:02:57.210
and if his appointment should become vacant,

63
00:02:57.730 --> 00:02:59.570
pray remind me of it.

64
00:02:59.730 --> 00:03:01.830
Oh, this is too much.

65
00:03:02.350 --> 00:03:05.670
Don Carlo, grandmaster of the royal lap

66
00:03:05.670 --> 00:03:06.030
-dogs?

67
00:03:06.810 --> 00:03:09.350
Oh, could I ever aspire to such a

68
00:03:09.350 --> 00:03:12.210
dignity, chief of the precious pets?

69
00:03:12.710 --> 00:03:14.790
Can I be worthy of such a position?

70
00:03:15.390 --> 00:03:18.570
Your peculiar talents design you for the

71
00:03:18.570 --> 00:03:19.210
situation.

72
00:03:19.810 --> 00:03:21.570
Pointing to Marchioness.

73
00:03:22.070 --> 00:03:24.510
But, my dear Marquis, do you see those

74
00:03:24.510 --> 00:03:27.530
two young tall gallants paying attention to

75
00:03:27.530 --> 00:03:29.290
that lovely wife of yours?

76
00:03:30.250 --> 00:03:33.350
Upon my honour, I think she grows younger

77
00:03:33.350 --> 00:03:34.490
every day.

78
00:03:35.010 --> 00:03:37.190
He turns away and approaches Maritana.

79
00:03:37.590 --> 00:03:39.730
He too is struck with the beauty of

80
00:03:39.730 --> 00:03:40.310
my wife.

81
00:03:40.970 --> 00:03:43.530
Poor young creature, she little knows the

82
00:03:43.530 --> 00:03:45.750
havoc she is making with her charms.

83
00:03:46.030 --> 00:03:47.670
Don José to Maritana.

84
00:03:47.670 --> 00:03:49.330
You seem thoughtful.

85
00:03:50.010 --> 00:03:51.950
Are you not pleased with the fate?

86
00:03:52.610 --> 00:03:54.990
There is all that wealth and taste could

87
00:03:54.990 --> 00:03:55.750
bring together.

88
00:03:56.190 --> 00:03:57.550
Nothing is wanting.

89
00:03:58.190 --> 00:04:00.130
Maritana, partly aside.

90
00:04:00.570 --> 00:04:04.030
Nothing is wanting, but one whose absence

91
00:04:04.030 --> 00:04:07.210
leaves a void within my heart makes me

92
00:04:07.210 --> 00:04:09.770
loathe the splendour which surrounds me.

93
00:04:10.450 --> 00:04:12.850
A servant comes down and speaks aside to

94
00:04:12.850 --> 00:04:13.490
Don José.

95
00:04:14.190 --> 00:04:16.850
The person whom your lordship expected has

96
00:04:16.850 --> 00:04:17.410
arrived.

97
00:04:17.670 --> 00:04:18.930
Goes up.

98
00:04:19.290 --> 00:04:20.170
Tis well.

99
00:04:20.670 --> 00:04:22.270
Aside to Marquis.

100
00:04:23.270 --> 00:04:25.670
Get rid of these people at once.

101
00:04:26.290 --> 00:04:27.390
Marquis aside.

102
00:04:28.070 --> 00:04:28.690
At once?

103
00:04:29.090 --> 00:04:30.970
That's rather unceremonious.

104
00:04:31.510 --> 00:04:32.830
But it must be done.

105
00:04:33.270 --> 00:04:33.830
Allowed.

106
00:04:34.390 --> 00:04:36.710
Gentlemen, pray lead your partners to the

107
00:04:36.710 --> 00:04:37.530
adjoining room.

108
00:04:38.150 --> 00:04:40.690
There is something provided there which, I

109
00:04:40.690 --> 00:04:43.430
flatter myself, will gratify and astonish

110
00:04:43.430 --> 00:04:43.830
you.

111
00:04:44.270 --> 00:04:44.910
Aside.

112
00:04:45.590 --> 00:04:47.030
Sandwiches and wine?

113
00:04:47.030 --> 00:04:48.090
Music.

114
00:04:48.510 --> 00:04:50.570
All the guests go off left centre.

115
00:04:50.970 --> 00:04:52.590
It was necessary to get rid of them,

116
00:04:52.910 --> 00:04:54.310
as Don José desired it.

117
00:04:55.010 --> 00:04:56.430
That wine must do it.

118
00:04:56.710 --> 00:04:58.790
The Marquis and Marchioness are about to

119
00:04:58.790 --> 00:05:01.470
follow guests, when Don José stops them.

120
00:05:01.690 --> 00:05:04.350
The lovely countess had better remain here.

121
00:05:04.950 --> 00:05:07.370
Will you also oblige me by doing so,

122
00:05:07.510 --> 00:05:08.610
my good host?

123
00:05:09.090 --> 00:05:09.550
Certainly.

124
00:05:09.970 --> 00:05:11.970
It is we that are obliged.

125
00:05:12.370 --> 00:05:14.730
I am particularly obliged.

126
00:05:15.270 --> 00:05:17.850
Don José aside to Maritana.

127
00:05:18.290 --> 00:05:21.490
This fate shall be complete, even to his

128
00:05:21.490 --> 00:05:24.350
presence, whose absence leaves a void and

129
00:05:24.350 --> 00:05:26.250
makes this splendour nothing.

130
00:05:26.930 --> 00:05:28.990
Exit Lady Marchioness left centre.

131
00:05:29.690 --> 00:05:31.210
Maritana to Marquis.

132
00:05:31.870 --> 00:05:35.070
Did you hear his lordship's last words?

133
00:05:35.490 --> 00:05:37.090
You are the host.

134
00:05:37.650 --> 00:05:39.970
Tis you that invite the guests.

135
00:05:40.670 --> 00:05:42.570
Will it be as Don José has promised?

136
00:05:43.130 --> 00:05:44.630
I dare say it will.

137
00:05:45.030 --> 00:05:45.590
Aside.

138
00:05:46.010 --> 00:05:48.130
I did not hear what Don José said,

139
00:05:48.310 --> 00:05:50.250
but I think it was my duty nevertheless

140
00:05:50.250 --> 00:05:51.390
to echo it.

141
00:05:51.590 --> 00:05:53.510
What does this all mean?

142
00:05:53.990 --> 00:05:55.350
Why this mystery?

143
00:05:55.950 --> 00:05:58.930
This marriage which I was told was the

144
00:05:58.930 --> 00:06:02.270
wish of the Queen, my gracious benefactress?

145
00:06:02.890 --> 00:06:04.950
If I ask to see the Queen, I

146
00:06:04.950 --> 00:06:06.050
am told to wait.

147
00:06:06.230 --> 00:06:09.290
If I enquire where is the husband to

148
00:06:09.290 --> 00:06:12.750
whom I was so mysteriously united, whether

149
00:06:12.750 --> 00:06:16.150
he is an exile, whether he is alive,

150
00:06:16.410 --> 00:06:19.630
when he will return, I am told to

151
00:06:19.630 --> 00:06:20.170
wait.

152
00:06:20.570 --> 00:06:22.530
Always the same reply.

153
00:06:23.250 --> 00:06:26.090
Tell me, Marquis, am I deceived?

154
00:06:26.730 --> 00:06:29.010
Has Don José been deceiving me?

155
00:06:29.250 --> 00:06:31.710
I hope not, for if he has deceived

156
00:06:31.710 --> 00:06:34.850
you, he is capable of deceiving me, and

157
00:06:34.850 --> 00:06:37.210
my hopes with regard to the royal lapdogs

158
00:06:37.210 --> 00:06:38.910
would be blighted for ever.

159
00:06:39.660 --> 00:06:41.730
But have you never seen your husband since

160
00:06:41.730 --> 00:06:42.530
you married him?

161
00:06:43.030 --> 00:06:45.170
I did not see him then.

162
00:06:45.590 --> 00:06:48.330
Your love must have been particularly blind.

163
00:06:48.830 --> 00:06:49.970
Not so.

164
00:06:50.210 --> 00:06:53.210
It was his generosity that I admired.

165
00:06:53.550 --> 00:06:54.870
Enter Don José's centre.

166
00:06:55.410 --> 00:06:58.690
That inspired in me the strongest interest

167
00:06:58.690 --> 00:06:59.590
towards him.

168
00:07:00.090 --> 00:07:02.530
For my sake he has suffered much, perhaps

169
00:07:02.530 --> 00:07:03.630
suffers now.

170
00:07:03.870 --> 00:07:06.910
I will demand of Don José when shall

171
00:07:06.910 --> 00:07:09.550
I see the Queen, when shall I see

172
00:07:09.550 --> 00:07:10.410
my husband?

173
00:07:10.830 --> 00:07:12.710
Don José coming down centre.

174
00:07:13.050 --> 00:07:13.910
I am glad.

175
00:07:14.090 --> 00:07:15.910
I am just in time to answer the

176
00:07:15.910 --> 00:07:16.370
question.

177
00:07:16.610 --> 00:07:19.730
Lady, you shall see your husband to-day.

178
00:07:20.170 --> 00:07:20.710
To-day?

179
00:07:21.050 --> 00:07:23.130
Marquis, aside to Don José.

180
00:07:23.530 --> 00:07:25.570
Isn't he dead then, after all?

181
00:07:25.750 --> 00:07:26.250
Silence.

182
00:07:26.890 --> 00:07:29.030
Surely, Count, I must have misunderstood

183
00:07:29.030 --> 00:07:29.810
you.

184
00:07:30.050 --> 00:07:32.030
Be calm, and listen to what I am

185
00:07:32.030 --> 00:07:32.990
about to say.

186
00:07:33.270 --> 00:07:34.650
Now I shall hear something.

187
00:07:35.210 --> 00:07:36.150
Now then.

188
00:07:36.150 --> 00:07:38.770
He is approaching to listen when Don José

189
00:07:38.770 --> 00:07:41.150
makes a sign to him to retire.

190
00:07:41.950 --> 00:07:44.230
He does so with an air of disappointment,

191
00:07:44.950 --> 00:07:46.930
bowed up centre by Don José.

192
00:07:47.410 --> 00:07:49.530
You wished us to be alone.

193
00:07:50.050 --> 00:07:52.450
Now let me hear of my husband.

194
00:07:53.070 --> 00:07:54.050
Don José right.

195
00:07:54.270 --> 00:07:55.710
He is at hand.

196
00:07:56.210 --> 00:07:58.550
The King enters centre from right.

197
00:07:59.050 --> 00:08:01.530
He is compelled to keep himself concealed,

198
00:08:02.210 --> 00:08:05.070
being in hourly danger from the law, for

199
00:08:05.070 --> 00:08:07.570
your sake, and for your sake alone he

200
00:08:07.570 --> 00:08:08.870
has ventured here.

201
00:08:09.430 --> 00:08:10.510
Crosses up left.

202
00:08:10.970 --> 00:08:13.090
Oh, we will find him a place of

203
00:08:13.090 --> 00:08:13.590
refuge.

204
00:08:14.130 --> 00:08:14.970
Where is he?

205
00:08:15.310 --> 00:08:15.690
Here.

206
00:08:16.370 --> 00:08:19.050
The King advances, puts his cloak off on

207
00:08:19.050 --> 00:08:20.250
chair, right centre.

208
00:08:21.190 --> 00:08:23.790
Maritana recoils with an exclamation.

209
00:08:24.650 --> 00:08:25.510
King right.

210
00:08:25.830 --> 00:08:29.910
Lady Maritana, do you not recollect me?

211
00:08:30.530 --> 00:08:31.890
Maritana aside.

212
00:08:32.590 --> 00:08:33.190
He?

213
00:08:33.750 --> 00:08:34.510
To Don José.

214
00:08:35.100 --> 00:08:36.950
That is not my husband.

215
00:08:37.330 --> 00:08:39.700
He to whom I gave my hand was—

216
00:08:40.250 --> 00:08:41.950
Don José left aside.

217
00:08:42.390 --> 00:08:45.330
Don César de Besen, behold him there.

218
00:08:45.670 --> 00:08:47.890
No, no, I never felt an interest but

219
00:08:47.890 --> 00:08:51.390
for one, and he, you told me, was

220
00:08:51.390 --> 00:08:52.730
Don César.

221
00:08:53.050 --> 00:08:55.530
I did but deceive you for your good.

222
00:08:56.110 --> 00:08:57.150
Gets up centre.

223
00:08:57.670 --> 00:08:59.770
Oh, wretched Maritana.

224
00:09:00.250 --> 00:09:02.670
Do you not remember, in a public place,

225
00:09:03.110 --> 00:09:06.790
one whose eyes followed you wherever you

226
00:09:06.790 --> 00:09:07.490
moved?

227
00:09:07.830 --> 00:09:11.670
One who of all the multitude around was

228
00:09:11.670 --> 00:09:15.630
alone charmed by the melancholy of your

229
00:09:15.630 --> 00:09:16.350
songs?

230
00:09:17.050 --> 00:09:18.850
I remember you, señor.

231
00:09:19.270 --> 00:09:19.890
Aside.

232
00:09:20.230 --> 00:09:22.930
For I trembled whilst I sought his bounty.

233
00:09:23.350 --> 00:09:26.510
It was because I loved you, it was

234
00:09:26.510 --> 00:09:30.510
because my happiness was centred all in you,

235
00:09:30.510 --> 00:09:33.710
that I determined to raise you to the

236
00:09:33.710 --> 00:09:35.630
station which you coveted.

237
00:09:36.250 --> 00:09:39.290
I resolved that you should share my love

238
00:09:39.290 --> 00:09:41.610
and— Don José centre interrupting.

239
00:09:42.070 --> 00:09:45.370
But being then prescribed, Don César could

240
00:09:45.370 --> 00:09:47.390
offer you nothing but his name.

241
00:09:47.690 --> 00:09:50.050
But now we meet again, under happier

242
00:09:50.050 --> 00:09:50.830
influences.

243
00:09:51.770 --> 00:09:55.450
Give me but one word, one look, to

244
00:09:55.450 --> 00:09:58.510
bid me hope for your love, and you

245
00:09:58.510 --> 00:10:00.430
shall be my sovereign mistress.

246
00:10:01.410 --> 00:10:05.230
I will live for you, yes, for you

247
00:10:05.230 --> 00:10:06.450
alone.

248
00:10:07.030 --> 00:10:07.970
Passionately.

249
00:10:08.530 --> 00:10:12.550
Don César, remember someone may overhear.

250
00:10:13.090 --> 00:10:16.970
Lovely Maritana, our return must be unknown,

251
00:10:17.790 --> 00:10:21.190
but my danger need not separate me from

252
00:10:21.190 --> 00:10:21.670
you.

253
00:10:22.110 --> 00:10:25.430
We can be happy separated from the world.

254
00:10:25.870 --> 00:10:27.570
Let us hence together.

255
00:10:28.490 --> 00:10:28.590
Together?

256
00:10:28.950 --> 00:10:31.570
A few miles from Madrid, there is a

257
00:10:31.570 --> 00:10:35.270
retreat where love may revel in security.

258
00:10:36.450 --> 00:10:38.170
Thither let us fly.

259
00:10:38.790 --> 00:10:40.510
Don José looking off right.

260
00:10:40.830 --> 00:10:42.010
You must not delay.

261
00:10:42.550 --> 00:10:44.790
The guests will soon grow weary of the

262
00:10:44.790 --> 00:10:45.270
dance.

263
00:10:45.650 --> 00:10:47.250
My Maritana, come.

264
00:10:47.810 --> 00:10:50.390
Why this ungenerous hesitation?

265
00:10:51.230 --> 00:10:52.510
Maritana aside.

266
00:10:53.050 --> 00:10:53.910
Oh, heaven!

267
00:10:54.550 --> 00:10:55.310
Allowed.

268
00:10:55.850 --> 00:10:58.030
But to leave thus suddenly, without even

269
00:10:58.030 --> 00:10:59.990
saying farewell to the Marquis.

270
00:11:00.510 --> 00:11:01.750
Don José aside.

271
00:11:02.550 --> 00:11:04.210
The guests are returning.

272
00:11:04.890 --> 00:11:05.430
Allowed.

273
00:11:05.910 --> 00:11:08.330
Don César, the Countess is right.

274
00:11:08.690 --> 00:11:10.150
It might awaken suspicion.

275
00:11:10.650 --> 00:11:12.630
If she were to quit the fate thus

276
00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:14.870
suddenly, she will follow you.

277
00:11:15.330 --> 00:11:17.710
A carriage will be waiting at the door

278
00:11:17.710 --> 00:11:18.850
of yonder garden.

279
00:11:19.510 --> 00:11:21.370
Remember your lover.

280
00:11:21.930 --> 00:11:23.830
Don José looks at him.

281
00:11:24.550 --> 00:11:27.690
Your husband waits for you.

282
00:11:27.890 --> 00:11:28.810
Someone comes.

283
00:11:29.010 --> 00:11:30.610
Quick, quick, be gone.

284
00:11:32.210 --> 00:11:34.690
Takes King's cloak from chair and puts it

285
00:11:34.690 --> 00:11:35.210
on him.

286
00:11:36.270 --> 00:11:38.270
Ladies and gentlemen cross from left to

287
00:11:38.270 --> 00:11:38.630
right.

288
00:11:39.070 --> 00:11:41.370
Oh, I am justly punished.

289
00:11:42.130 --> 00:11:44.870
Oh, I hate these golds purchased, as they

290
00:11:44.870 --> 00:11:46.890
must be by days of misery.

291
00:11:47.930 --> 00:11:48.410
Music.

292
00:11:48.990 --> 00:11:52.070
The King exits rapidly centre and off right.

293
00:11:53.110 --> 00:11:55.830
The Marchioness enters, and at a signal from

294
00:11:55.830 --> 00:11:59.230
Don José, leads out Maritana, who is in

295
00:11:59.230 --> 00:12:01.010
tears, left centre.

296
00:12:01.410 --> 00:12:04.810
How every obstacle that stood between me and

297
00:12:04.810 --> 00:12:07.670
my desire melts into the air.

298
00:12:08.070 --> 00:12:11.190
Don César enters in the disguise of a

299
00:12:11.190 --> 00:12:13.290
monk, centre left.

300
00:12:13.770 --> 00:12:16.930
Don César approaching Don José with great

301
00:12:16.930 --> 00:12:17.650
humility.

302
00:12:17.650 --> 00:12:20.530
Arms for our monastery's son.

303
00:12:20.930 --> 00:12:22.530
Don José crosses to left.

304
00:12:22.690 --> 00:12:26.310
So, Don José, here I am once more.

305
00:12:26.730 --> 00:12:29.110
Throwing off disguise and discovering

306
00:12:29.110 --> 00:12:29.670
himself.

307
00:12:30.170 --> 00:12:33.230
You, Don César, not dead.

308
00:12:33.530 --> 00:12:34.610
Not yet.

309
00:12:34.890 --> 00:12:36.230
Who saved your life?

310
00:12:36.490 --> 00:12:39.810
You did, by rescuing me from the gallows.

311
00:12:40.030 --> 00:12:42.270
But I saw you led out to execution.

312
00:12:42.710 --> 00:12:44.070
I heard the muskets.

313
00:12:44.350 --> 00:12:45.610
So did I.

314
00:12:45.890 --> 00:12:46.430
Aside.

315
00:12:46.430 --> 00:12:49.050
And here are the bullets extracted in good

316
00:12:49.050 --> 00:12:53.330
time from the guns by my faithful Lazarelle

317
00:12:53.330 --> 00:12:53.830
Lowe.

318
00:12:54.290 --> 00:12:56.750
Shorts bag containing bullets.

319
00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:58.430
Yes, here they are.

320
00:12:58.630 --> 00:12:59.350
Six in number.

321
00:12:59.730 --> 00:13:01.610
They're better in my pocket than in my

322
00:13:01.610 --> 00:13:01.970
body.

323
00:13:02.650 --> 00:13:05.030
I never expected to receive them with so

324
00:13:05.030 --> 00:13:06.630
much satisfaction.

325
00:13:07.230 --> 00:13:08.250
Crosses left.

326
00:13:08.630 --> 00:13:09.770
But you fell.

327
00:13:10.150 --> 00:13:10.950
Of course I did.

328
00:13:11.210 --> 00:13:13.650
I could not do less when six gallant

329
00:13:13.650 --> 00:13:15.550
soldiers took the trouble to make me their

330
00:13:15.550 --> 00:13:15.950
target.

331
00:13:16.430 --> 00:13:18.970
I should have wounded their pride if I

332
00:13:18.970 --> 00:13:20.690
had made them think they had missed their

333
00:13:20.690 --> 00:13:21.150
aim.

334
00:13:21.510 --> 00:13:23.310
I have been deceived.

335
00:13:23.750 --> 00:13:24.970
And so have I.

336
00:13:25.210 --> 00:13:27.530
The illusion was so perfect that I really

337
00:13:27.530 --> 00:13:28.430
thought I was dead.

338
00:13:29.110 --> 00:13:32.210
And consequently, all my creditors paid.

339
00:13:32.870 --> 00:13:35.290
Till I found myself among some of my

340
00:13:35.290 --> 00:13:38.170
old companions with a dice box in my

341
00:13:38.170 --> 00:13:39.970
hand and a flagon before me.

342
00:13:40.230 --> 00:13:40.990
Crosses right.

343
00:13:41.670 --> 00:13:43.470
Who can have betrayed me?

344
00:13:43.790 --> 00:13:45.210
Don César aside.

345
00:13:45.210 --> 00:13:48.190
Thank heavens he does not suspect the dear

346
00:13:48.190 --> 00:13:48.670
boy.

347
00:13:49.010 --> 00:13:52.570
Sitting down unceremoniously, aloud.

348
00:13:52.750 --> 00:13:54.350
There seems to be a fate here.

349
00:13:54.570 --> 00:13:55.190
There is.

350
00:13:55.550 --> 00:13:56.850
You are in danger.

351
00:13:57.190 --> 00:13:58.290
Why did you come?

352
00:13:58.490 --> 00:14:00.290
I'll tell you if you'll have a little

353
00:14:00.290 --> 00:14:00.830
patience.

354
00:14:01.390 --> 00:14:03.130
I happen to see a carriage with my

355
00:14:03.130 --> 00:14:04.690
own arms upon it.

356
00:14:05.170 --> 00:14:07.670
And on enquiry, I found it belonged to

357
00:14:07.670 --> 00:14:08.890
the Countess de Bazin.

358
00:14:09.430 --> 00:14:10.510
So here I am.

359
00:14:11.310 --> 00:14:12.190
Where's my wife?

360
00:14:12.710 --> 00:14:15.250
For you know I've not much time to

361
00:14:15.250 --> 00:14:18.130
lose if the sentence of that cursed edict

362
00:14:18.130 --> 00:14:19.290
is to be respected.

363
00:14:19.910 --> 00:14:20.950
Don José aside.

364
00:14:21.130 --> 00:14:23.110
He is not aware of his pardon.

365
00:14:23.690 --> 00:14:25.530
Allowed with dignity.

366
00:14:26.170 --> 00:14:29.030
Tell me, Don César, what are your plans?

367
00:14:29.230 --> 00:14:30.110
To see my wife.

368
00:14:30.530 --> 00:14:31.170
She's mine.

369
00:14:31.510 --> 00:14:33.570
And I may as well take possession.

370
00:14:34.110 --> 00:14:36.170
You gave her to me and I have

371
00:14:36.170 --> 00:14:39.990
come to you, therefore, to profit by your

372
00:14:39.990 --> 00:14:40.750
benevolence.

373
00:14:40.750 --> 00:14:42.430
Don José aside.

374
00:14:42.950 --> 00:14:45.750
Must all my designs be thus o'erthrown?

375
00:14:46.050 --> 00:14:48.330
No, it shall not be.

376
00:14:48.770 --> 00:14:50.630
Into Marquis' Centre from left.

377
00:14:50.990 --> 00:14:52.450
My guests are merry fellows.

378
00:14:53.070 --> 00:14:55.110
They do nothing but drink to the Countess

379
00:14:55.110 --> 00:14:55.870
de Bazin.

380
00:14:56.470 --> 00:14:57.830
Don César right.

381
00:14:58.170 --> 00:14:59.290
The deuce they do.

382
00:14:59.670 --> 00:15:01.450
The Countess de Bazin, my wife.

383
00:15:01.930 --> 00:15:02.670
Where is she?

384
00:15:02.910 --> 00:15:03.670
I beg pardon.

385
00:15:04.130 --> 00:15:05.470
Are you Don César?

386
00:15:06.150 --> 00:15:09.170
Are you the gentleman that is not dead?

387
00:15:09.510 --> 00:15:10.650
Don José left.

388
00:15:10.750 --> 00:15:12.250
Aside to Marquis.

389
00:15:12.650 --> 00:15:13.210
Not a word.

390
00:15:13.690 --> 00:15:14.710
Not another word.

391
00:15:15.270 --> 00:15:17.670
Evince no astonishment at anything you hear

392
00:15:17.670 --> 00:15:18.290
or see.

393
00:15:18.790 --> 00:15:20.390
Do as I wish.

394
00:15:20.850 --> 00:15:21.630
Crosses left.

395
00:15:22.190 --> 00:15:23.270
And the left dogs?

396
00:15:23.570 --> 00:15:24.630
Shall be yours.

397
00:15:24.950 --> 00:15:26.530
Crosses to Don César.

398
00:15:27.270 --> 00:15:27.930
Allowed.

399
00:15:28.390 --> 00:15:31.870
Don César, your rights are sacred and they

400
00:15:31.870 --> 00:15:32.910
shall be respected.

401
00:15:33.510 --> 00:15:36.490
Your wife, the Countess de Bazin, is here

402
00:15:36.490 --> 00:15:38.490
and shall join you immediately.

403
00:15:39.070 --> 00:15:40.030
Wait for her.

404
00:15:40.030 --> 00:15:42.350
Exit centre and off right.

405
00:15:42.570 --> 00:15:45.450
She comes and I shall see her as

406
00:15:45.450 --> 00:15:48.190
I have seen her in my dreams, radiant

407
00:15:48.190 --> 00:15:49.690
in youth and beauty.

408
00:15:50.230 --> 00:15:51.590
The Marquis is going.

409
00:15:52.010 --> 00:15:54.030
Stay near me, sir, and support me.

410
00:15:54.330 --> 00:15:56.210
I am sure I shall require it.

411
00:15:56.550 --> 00:15:58.610
The rapture will be too much for me.

412
00:15:58.830 --> 00:16:01.550
The soft white hand haunts me like a

413
00:16:01.550 --> 00:16:02.150
spectre.

414
00:16:02.470 --> 00:16:04.790
Enter Don José, leading and Marchioness.

415
00:16:05.190 --> 00:16:06.090
Centre from left.

416
00:16:06.890 --> 00:16:08.630
Marquis to Don César.

417
00:16:08.630 --> 00:16:09.890
Don't agitate yourself.

418
00:16:10.090 --> 00:16:10.870
Be calm.

419
00:16:11.250 --> 00:16:12.750
I know what it is to await the

420
00:16:12.750 --> 00:16:13.870
coming of a lovely woman.

421
00:16:14.590 --> 00:16:16.050
I have a Marchioness.

422
00:16:16.350 --> 00:16:19.110
Don José looking significantly at the

423
00:16:19.110 --> 00:16:19.590
Marquis.

424
00:16:19.930 --> 00:16:23.510
Don César, behold the Countess de Bazin.

425
00:16:23.730 --> 00:16:25.190
Presents Marchioness.

426
00:16:25.850 --> 00:16:26.770
The Countess?

427
00:16:27.210 --> 00:16:27.830
The devil.

428
00:16:28.110 --> 00:16:29.430
Marquis aside.

429
00:16:30.330 --> 00:16:31.650
He's giving him my wife.

430
00:16:32.110 --> 00:16:33.650
The Marchioness smiles.

431
00:16:34.590 --> 00:16:35.570
She likes it.

432
00:16:35.890 --> 00:16:37.830
Don César bows formally.

433
00:16:38.710 --> 00:16:39.310
Aside.

434
00:16:39.590 --> 00:16:42.810
No wonder she wore a veil—sixty by the

435
00:16:42.810 --> 00:16:43.150
mass.

436
00:16:43.590 --> 00:16:44.470
He struck with her.

437
00:16:44.970 --> 00:16:46.390
Don César to Marquis.

438
00:16:46.730 --> 00:16:49.690
Will you—will you show me the nearest way

439
00:16:49.690 --> 00:16:50.450
to the door?

440
00:16:50.770 --> 00:16:54.030
Don César, the Countess de Bazin is prepared

441
00:16:54.030 --> 00:16:56.590
to fulfil all the duties of a wife

442
00:16:56.590 --> 00:16:59.030
to him, who has a right to demand

443
00:16:59.030 --> 00:16:59.370
them.

444
00:16:59.570 --> 00:17:01.630
I trust you will make no sacrifice on

445
00:17:01.630 --> 00:17:02.330
my account.

446
00:17:02.870 --> 00:17:04.390
Marchioness turns away.

447
00:17:05.010 --> 00:17:05.869
To Don José.

448
00:17:05.869 --> 00:17:08.069
You can make out another warrant for my

449
00:17:08.069 --> 00:17:08.690
execution.

450
00:17:09.390 --> 00:17:11.270
I should prefer it to this.

451
00:17:11.650 --> 00:17:12.230
To Marquis.

452
00:17:12.589 --> 00:17:15.310
My good friend, did you ever see such

453
00:17:15.310 --> 00:17:16.530
a perfect gorgon?

454
00:17:17.170 --> 00:17:18.490
Frightful, isn't she?

455
00:17:18.750 --> 00:17:19.670
Marquis aside.

456
00:17:20.250 --> 00:17:21.670
Frightful, Don César.

457
00:17:22.130 --> 00:17:24.430
The man's troubles have ruined his eyesight.

458
00:17:24.690 --> 00:17:26.390
The Countess awaits your bidding.

459
00:17:26.869 --> 00:17:29.530
She's prepared to share your state and

460
00:17:29.530 --> 00:17:30.430
fortunes.

461
00:17:30.430 --> 00:17:33.610
Madam, I will not take advantage of the

462
00:17:33.610 --> 00:17:34.770
accident of fate.

463
00:17:35.350 --> 00:17:37.810
Charmed as I must be at the generosity

464
00:17:37.810 --> 00:17:40.150
of the her who would share the lot

465
00:17:40.150 --> 00:17:43.410
of so poor, so dunned, so desperate a

466
00:17:43.410 --> 00:17:44.990
libertine as myself.

467
00:17:45.450 --> 00:17:48.030
She knew your position when she consented to

468
00:17:48.030 --> 00:17:48.610
the union.

469
00:17:48.910 --> 00:17:49.510
Did she?

470
00:17:50.130 --> 00:17:53.850
Then I will not be outdone in generosity.

471
00:17:54.350 --> 00:17:55.290
Crosses aside.

472
00:17:55.290 --> 00:17:57.870
Madam, I will not take you from those

473
00:17:57.870 --> 00:18:00.690
to whom you are endeared by years.

474
00:18:02.170 --> 00:18:04.610
Long years of tender association.

475
00:18:05.550 --> 00:18:07.990
At your age, I mean, that is.

476
00:18:08.270 --> 00:18:11.410
In fact, madam, I free you from every

477
00:18:11.410 --> 00:18:11.830
tie.

478
00:18:12.190 --> 00:18:14.130
I am no longer a husband.

479
00:18:16.750 --> 00:18:19.210
Did you ever see such infernal wrinkles?

480
00:18:21.810 --> 00:18:22.410
Aside.

481
00:18:25.550 --> 00:18:29.050
Perhaps, madam, at some distant period, some

482
00:18:29.050 --> 00:18:30.970
very distant period.

483
00:18:31.190 --> 00:18:32.530
She turns to him.

484
00:18:32.770 --> 00:18:34.490
No, I can never venture.

485
00:18:34.870 --> 00:18:35.670
The two Marquis.

486
00:18:36.110 --> 00:18:39.350
As a reasonable man, Marquis, I ask you,

487
00:18:39.830 --> 00:18:42.450
if on any consideration in the world you

488
00:18:42.450 --> 00:18:45.230
would call that venerable woman wife.

489
00:18:46.710 --> 00:18:47.390
Aside.

490
00:18:48.350 --> 00:18:49.870
This is too bad.

491
00:18:50.210 --> 00:18:50.850
Allowed.

492
00:18:50.850 --> 00:18:53.910
If you don't like her yourself, you needn't

493
00:18:53.910 --> 00:18:55.730
make other people dissatisfied.

494
00:18:56.190 --> 00:18:56.830
Other people?

495
00:18:57.670 --> 00:18:58.710
Is there any fool?

496
00:18:59.430 --> 00:19:02.370
Pray, let me not stand in anybody's way.

497
00:19:02.790 --> 00:19:05.370
Don José, who has conversed apart with the

498
00:19:05.370 --> 00:19:06.090
Marchioness.

499
00:19:06.430 --> 00:19:08.570
Come, let us end this business.

500
00:19:09.070 --> 00:19:09.850
Crosses left.

501
00:19:10.430 --> 00:19:13.170
You know, Don Cesar, that the object of

502
00:19:13.170 --> 00:19:15.270
this marriage was your title and not

503
00:19:15.270 --> 00:19:15.930
yourself.

504
00:19:16.170 --> 00:19:18.970
I am willing to stand by that bargain.

505
00:19:18.970 --> 00:19:22.010
At your nuptials, you had scarcely ten

506
00:19:22.010 --> 00:19:22.870
minutes to live.

507
00:19:23.090 --> 00:19:25.210
Ah, I was happier then than I am

508
00:19:25.210 --> 00:19:25.610
now.

509
00:19:25.910 --> 00:19:27.990
The Countess does not love you.

510
00:19:28.270 --> 00:19:31.530
What wonderful unanimity in man and wife.

511
00:19:31.810 --> 00:19:34.090
Your chains may yet be golden ones.

512
00:19:34.610 --> 00:19:35.750
Your wife is rich.

513
00:19:36.090 --> 00:19:36.870
You have nothing.

514
00:19:37.270 --> 00:19:39.810
Your estimate of my property is singularly

515
00:19:39.810 --> 00:19:40.650
exact.

516
00:19:41.010 --> 00:19:43.470
You shall have a pension of six thousand

517
00:19:43.470 --> 00:19:46.030
piastres if you quit Madrid forever.

518
00:19:46.410 --> 00:19:47.070
Quit Madrid?

519
00:19:47.590 --> 00:19:49.790
The city of my birth, the home of

520
00:19:49.790 --> 00:19:50.870
my creditors.

521
00:19:51.510 --> 00:19:53.490
The last apostrophe has decided me.

522
00:19:53.730 --> 00:19:54.310
I'll go.

523
00:19:54.970 --> 00:19:57.750
You must also renounce all right acquired by

524
00:19:57.750 --> 00:19:58.510
your marriage.

525
00:19:58.890 --> 00:20:01.350
Forgo the bliss of— Peeps at the

526
00:20:01.350 --> 00:20:02.110
Marchioness.

527
00:20:02.390 --> 00:20:03.010
It's a bargain.

528
00:20:03.270 --> 00:20:05.250
Will you sign a paper to that effect?

529
00:20:05.590 --> 00:20:07.810
Don Cesar hurries to table right.

530
00:20:08.030 --> 00:20:08.530
Will I?

531
00:20:09.210 --> 00:20:10.430
Dictate the terms.

532
00:20:10.810 --> 00:20:12.050
The more binding the better.

533
00:20:12.470 --> 00:20:14.050
Don José dictating.

534
00:20:14.610 --> 00:20:19.590
Don Cesar, Count de Garofa, engages on the

535
00:20:19.590 --> 00:20:22.530
honour of a gentleman to quit Madrid

536
00:20:22.530 --> 00:20:23.430
forever.

537
00:20:23.750 --> 00:20:25.470
Don Cesar pauses.

538
00:20:25.990 --> 00:20:26.410
Forever?

539
00:20:27.150 --> 00:20:28.850
My poor creditors.

540
00:20:29.270 --> 00:20:32.590
And renounces the Countess de Bazin, his

541
00:20:32.590 --> 00:20:33.030
wife.

542
00:20:33.330 --> 00:20:35.310
Six thousand piastres for that?

543
00:20:35.870 --> 00:20:37.950
I would have purchased the same advantages

544
00:20:37.950 --> 00:20:39.190
at double the amount.

545
00:20:39.530 --> 00:20:40.330
Right, sir.

546
00:20:40.430 --> 00:20:41.170
My wife.

547
00:20:41.170 --> 00:20:43.810
Never to claim the name of husband.

548
00:20:44.270 --> 00:20:45.510
Oh, never, never.

549
00:20:45.870 --> 00:20:46.350
Sign.

550
00:20:46.670 --> 00:20:50.410
Don C— A servant enters at back and

551
00:20:50.410 --> 00:20:51.450
calls left centre.

552
00:20:51.970 --> 00:20:54.490
The carriage of the Countess de Bazin.

553
00:20:55.030 --> 00:20:56.450
Don Cesar pauses.

554
00:20:56.830 --> 00:20:57.070
May?

555
00:20:57.590 --> 00:20:59.730
Sign, sign, Don Cesar.

556
00:21:00.050 --> 00:21:01.230
Goes up to him.

557
00:21:01.850 --> 00:21:04.650
Make way for the Countess de Bazin.

558
00:21:05.070 --> 00:21:07.610
Maritana passes it back from left to right,

559
00:21:07.950 --> 00:21:09.150
attended it by nobles.

560
00:21:09.150 --> 00:21:11.170
I have been deceived.

561
00:21:12.090 --> 00:21:13.590
What do I see?

562
00:21:14.090 --> 00:21:16.010
Maritana exits right centre.

563
00:21:16.870 --> 00:21:19.450
Don Cesar is about to follow when Don

564
00:21:19.450 --> 00:21:20.870
José interposes.

565
00:21:21.470 --> 00:21:22.710
Stay your signature.

566
00:21:23.290 --> 00:21:25.690
You have pledged the honour of a gentleman.

567
00:21:26.290 --> 00:21:28.270
Don Cesar tears the paper.

568
00:21:28.890 --> 00:21:30.350
I see the trick.

569
00:21:31.070 --> 00:21:31.330
There.

570
00:21:31.730 --> 00:21:34.610
Don Cesar, remember you are a condemned

571
00:21:34.610 --> 00:21:35.330
criminal.

572
00:21:35.710 --> 00:21:37.850
A word from me would be the signal

573
00:21:37.850 --> 00:21:39.230
of your death.

574
00:21:39.630 --> 00:21:42.270
At last you throw off the mask.

575
00:21:42.650 --> 00:21:45.070
Now we understand each other.

576
00:21:45.370 --> 00:21:46.810
Flight is still possible.

577
00:21:47.350 --> 00:21:49.490
I will aid you on one condition.

578
00:21:49.850 --> 00:21:53.010
No, no more shameful bargains.

579
00:21:53.450 --> 00:21:54.050
Be warned.

580
00:21:54.630 --> 00:21:57.350
Pursue your wife a single step and it

581
00:21:57.350 --> 00:21:59.110
will lead to your destruction.

582
00:21:59.610 --> 00:22:01.470
She is then my wife?

583
00:22:01.470 --> 00:22:04.290
Give me free passage or I shall owe

584
00:22:04.290 --> 00:22:05.770
the law another life.

585
00:22:06.010 --> 00:22:06.450
Away.

586
00:22:06.850 --> 00:22:08.950
Pushes him aside and rushes off.

587
00:22:09.270 --> 00:22:10.270
Oh, guards.

588
00:22:10.610 --> 00:22:10.950
Drum.

589
00:22:11.790 --> 00:22:13.290
Soldiers enter from left.

590
00:22:14.050 --> 00:22:15.090
Pursue that man.

591
00:22:15.650 --> 00:22:18.250
If he resists, fire upon him immediately.

592
00:22:19.870 --> 00:22:20.610
Music.

593
00:22:21.770 --> 00:22:22.730
General movement.

594
00:22:23.750 --> 00:22:24.470
Tableau.

595
00:22:25.670 --> 00:22:26.910
End of Act Two.
